<archetype>

  <archetypetitle>Hedge Wizard</archetypetitle>
  <archetypeid>hedge_wizard</archetypeid>
  <archetypedescription>     
    <p>
      Hedge Wizards are wandering mages, they make their money in side shows, by grifting, in displays
      of minor magical feats for the entertainment of young children, by providing mystic readings for
      young women and the love-lorn, or through the application of their craft in illegal or martial roles.
    </p>

    <figure>
      <img src="./resources/hedge_wizard/the_crooked_staff_by_dw_miller_by_conceptsbymiller-day36nr.png"
	   scale="0.28"/>
    </figure>        

    <p>
      The College of Mages offers membership to most powerful magical practitioners.  They
      are a political body that exists for the protection and advancement of its members.
      Hedge wizards are not members of the college, though they may become so later in their career.
    </p>

    <p>
      There are many reasons practioners may not be members of the College, they may have pursued
      their craft without drawing attention to themselves, they may have been excluded out of
      spite or jealousy from some member in power, they may wish to pursue their studies away from the eyes
      of others, or they may have been offered membership and rejected it.  Hedge wizards are usually left
      to their own business.  They are however required to be licensed as users of magick and produce said
      license upon request from the law.  They are required to practice their craft in accordance with a
      set of rules know as the Lex Arcanaum, which for example prohibts the practice of necromancy, mind
      control and the like. They are referred to officially as non-collegiate magical practitioners.
      Possesion of the license grants immunity from persecution by the Witch Hunters provided there
      has been infringement of the Lex Arcanum.
    </p>

  </archetypedescription>
  <archetypeprimaryabilities>
      <list> 
        <li>Str:-1, End:-1, Ag:+1, Spd:+0, Per:+2, or</li>
        <li>Str:+0, End:-1, Ag:+1, Spd:+0, Per:+1</li>
      </list>
  </archetypeprimaryabilities>
  <archetypeinitialabilities>
    <p>
      All Hedge Wizards start with the following skills: ✱language.merovingian_4, ✱language.inochian_2,
      ✱physical.dodge_2, ✱staff.strike_1, ✱sword.strike_1, ✱physical.run_2, ✱physical.notice_2, ✱physical.jump_1, ✱physical.climb_1, ✱arcana.lore_1,
      ✱conjuration.lore_1, ✱arcana.true_sight_1, and ✱luck.reroll_1.
    </p>

  </archetypeinitialabilities>
  <archetypemovedistance>6</archetypemovedistance>
  <startingcash>20 + d4 sp</startingcash>
  <startinggear>
    Cloak, staff, long sword, dagger, flint, Non-Collegiate Magical Practitioner License, rations for a week.
  </startinggear>
  
  <height>
    <metric>160 + 3d10 cm</metric>
    <imperial>4'8" + 2d8 inches</imperial>
  </height>
  <weight>
    <metric>50 + 3d10 kg</metric>
    <imperial>100 + 4d20 pounds</imperial>
  </weight>
  <age>24 + 2d6 years</age>

  <aspectexamples>Knowledge is Power, No One Must Know of My Work, The Smartest Man in the Room, I have been Chosen</aspectexamples>
  <archetypetags>
    <human/>
    <humanoid/>
    <medium/> 
    <magicuser/> 
  </archetypetags> 
  
  <archetypebio>
    <subsection>
      <subsectiontitle>Origin</subsectiontitle>
      <p>
    	Determine where the character came from by rolling once on the Homeland table below.
      </p>
      
      <table>
      	<tablecategory>Standard</tablecategory>
      	<tablespec>
      	  <fixed>0.94</fixed>
      	</tablespec>
      	<tabletitle>Homelands</tabletitle>

      	<tableheaderrow>
      	  <td>Homeland - Roll 1D12 </td>
      	</tableheaderrow>

      	<tablerow>
      	  <td><bold>1 Hybernia</bold>: ✱language.hybernian_3,  ✱social.etiquette[Hybernia]_3</td>
      	</tablerow>

      	<tablerow>
      	  <td><bold>2 Almaignee</bold>: ✱social.etiquette[Almaignee]_3</td>
      	</tablerow>
	
      	<tablerow>
      	  <td><bold>3 Poitevin</bold>: ✱language.poitevin_4, ✱social.etiquette[Averoigne]_3</td>
      	</tablerow>

      	<tablerow>
      	  <td><bold>4 Averoigne</bold>: One of ✱language.poitevin_4 or ✱language.occitan_4, ✱social.etiquette[Averoigne]_3</td>
      	</tablerow>

      	<tablerow>
      	  <td><bold>5 Albion</bold>: ✱language.hybernian_1, ✱social.etiquette[Albion]_3, ✱social.etiquette[Hybernia]_2,
	  ✱social.contacts[Albion]_2</td>
      	</tablerow>
	
      	<tablerow>
      	  <td><bold>6-11 Westreich</bold>: ✱social.etiquette[Westreich]_3, 
	  ✱social.contacts[Westreich]_2, ✱language.occitan_1 and ✱social.etiquette[Averoigne]_1,
	  or ✱language.hybernian_1 and ✱social.etiquette[Hybernia]_1</td>
      	</tablerow>

      	<tablerow>
      	  <td><bold>12 Choose</bold></td>
      	</tablerow>

      	<tablelabel>table:{{ doc_name }}-homeland</tablelabel>
      </table>
    </subsection>


    <subsection>
      <subsectiontitle>Study Tables</subsectiontitle>      
      <p>
	Roll once on each of the following tables.
      </p>      

      <table>
    	<tablecategory>Standard</tablecategory>
    	<tablespec>
    	  <fixed>0.18</fixed>
    	  <fixed>0.71</fixed>
    	</tablespec>
